The problem is that the lastEditor flag is extension specific. For UCEd, it should be false. For GRL, it should be true.

Actually, what should be done is an autolayout of the new maps, not only the last one. Therefore, if the file is new, all of the maps should have an autolayout performed. If it is a merge, the new maps should have one. Therefore, instead of passing in lastEditor, we should pass a list of map ids to be automatically layed out. We can compute this list by building a list when the URN is passed in to the import extension and comparing to what is there after the import. 

Diagrams deleted in the import should not be autolayed out, obviously.


Another thing, I'm not sure, but our editors might be sorted alphabetically, and not corresponding to the order they are in the model. Therefore, the lastEditor technique just doesn't work.

