1) I've added a preference to select between both types.
2) Internally, the same values are kept. This is to ensure that models can still be exchanged between computers and algorithms don't need to be changed. If the option is selected, the exports (& reports) use the right range.  
3) I did not touch the KPI values - not sure if this was required for this bug.
4) I did not touch the color schemes  - same as previous are still applicable (the new 0 still gets shown as red because internally it is -100). 

The code isn't easy to change so that it still looks good - these color ranges were hand crafted to ensure the entire range of changes is visible. 

